metadata.description:
I’ve always been kind of sad that I wasn’t releasing music in the golden era of Soundcloud that people always talk about. That time sounds like it was just special. Artists making cool music and uploading it right away. A quick feedback loop with musicians feeding off of each other's energy.

 It feels like we’re living through that kind of moment right now with Music NFTs, and I wanted to embrace this ethos for my second drop on Sound. So I made this song over the weekend. No tinkering with it for weeks before sharing. Just an idea from my DAW to your ears right away.

Artwork is from a cool spot I found hiking recently. It's a small cliff right next to some trees which makes it feel like you're in the treetops.

Thank you so much for your support.
metadata.name: In The Trees #1
metadata.title: In The Trees
